  "bodyLines": [
    "about the job",
    "about nira energy",
    "nira's mission is to help convert the us power grid to be 100% fossil-free.",
    "we are profitable!",
    "nira is a software platform that helps renewable energy developers find the cheapest points on the grid to connect.",
    "we focus on estimating the cost to interconnect with the electrical grid (aka the interconnection process). depending on where developers connect, they may be on the hook to pay millions of dollars to upgrade power lines, substations etc.",
    "what you'll do",
    "as a software engineer at nira, you'll work on software and data products that our customers use every week. your work will directly accelerate renewables getting built. this work could include rolling out new regions, adding new features or even building brand new products out.",
    "nira operates in the niche world of grid interconnection, which means as a swe, you'll get to learn about how new renewables get connected to the grid. day to day, you'll work very closely with transmission planning engineers (tpes) to get your job done. both the swes and tpes only have half the picture, so our teams have to be extremely cross-discipline and collaborative. most teams are structured with 1 pm, 1 swe and 1 tpe.",
    "most of the code you'll write will be python data pipelines. there is occasionally some frontend work as well (having fe experience is not a requirement). however, the swes that do best here are the ones that don't really care what part of the stack they're working on - they're just excited to be building products that help fix climate.",
    "about you",
    "4+ years as a swe.",
    "mission-oriented and focused on working on climate.",
    "excited about working with transmission engineers.",
    "operate well in ambiguity and able to take ownership over large pieces of work.",
    "capable of rolling with the punches; plans change at a growing startup.",
    "python experience is a plus",
    "we are hiring any kind of swe, except for pure frontend engineers.",
    "this role can be remote, or in-person hybrid from our nyc office."
  ],
  "downweightedLines": [],
  "cleanTitle": "software engineer",
  "cleanBody": "about the job about nira energy nira's mission is to help convert the us power grid to be 100% fossil-free. we are profitable! nira is a software platform that helps renewable energy developers find the cheapest points on the grid to connect. we focus on estimating the cost to interconnect with the electrical grid (aka the interconnection process). depending on where developers connect, they may be on the hook to pay millions of dollars to upgrade power lines, substations etc. what you'll do as a software engineer at nira, you'll work on software and data products that our customers use every week. your work will directly accelerate renewables getting built. this work could include rolling out new regions, adding new features or even building brand new products out. nira operates in the niche world of grid interconnection, which means as a swe, you'll get to learn about how new renewables get connected to the grid. day to day, you'll work very closely with transmission planning engineers (tpes) to get your job done. both the swes and tpes only have half the picture, so our teams have to be extremely cross-discipline and collaborative. most teams are structured with 1 pm, 1 swe and 1 tpe. most of the code you'll write will be python . there is occasionally some frontend work as well (having fe experience is not a requirement). however, the swes that do best here are the ones that don't really care what part of the stack they're working on - they're just excited to be building products that help fix climate. about you 4+ years as a swe. mission-oriented and focused on working on climate. excited about working with transmission engineers. operate well in ambiguity and able to take ownership over large pieces of work. capable of rolling with the punches; plans change at a growing startup. python experience is a plus we are hiring any kind of swe, except for pure frontend engineers. this role can be remote, or in-person hybrid from our nyc office.",
